close_reason: "Shipped and verified: 19 slots stamped 2026.7.11 across 16 manifests; sync enforced at release time (pipeline apply) and in CI (version:check chain); 100%-coverage spec; contract-spec semver time bombs (minor>=4 Jan-Mar failure, ordinal-release regex) defused. All targeted vitest suites, eslint, claude plugin validate --strict, and the full plugin smoke pass."
body: "User directive 2026-07-11: pm-cli does NOT use semver — every plugin and package must carry the same date-based version (YYYY.M.D[-N]) as the root package.\n\n## What shipped\n\n1. **scripts/sync-versions.mjs** (new): `check` fails on any drift from the root package.json version; `apply` stamps the root version into every distribution-facing manifest. Discovers workspace packages dynamically (readdirSync), so new packages join the policy automatically. Refuses to propagate a non-date-based root version. Handles all three marketplace slot shapes (top-level version, metadata.version, plugins[].version) and only syncs slots that already exist — deleting a duplicate field later is never undone.\n2. **One-time alignment applied**: 19 version slots stamped 2026.7.11 across 16 files — 11 packages/*/package.json (0.1.0, all private), plugins/pm-claude/.claude-plugin/plugin.json (1.4.1), plugins/pm-codex/.codex-plugin/plugin.json (1.1.0), .claude-plugin/marketplace.json + root marketplace.json (metadata.version + plugins[0].version), .agents/plugins/marketplace.json (both entries).\n3. **Release pipeline** (scripts/release/run-release-pipeline.mjs): runs `sync-versions.mjs apply` immediately after the root `npm version` bump and stages the synced manifests in the release commit — plugins/packages can never drift again; marketplace users now receive a plugin update with every release (was frozen at 1.4.1 since 2026-07-02).\n4. **CI gate**: `pnpm version:check` (already in CI Gates static) now chains `sync-versions.mjs check`; new `pnpm version:sync` convenience script.\n5. **tests/unit/scripts/sync-versions.spec.ts** (new): 6 scenarios, 100% lines/branches/functions on the script (repo scripts sit under the 100% coverage gate).\n6. **tests/integration/claude-plugin-contract.spec.ts**: replaced two latent semver-era time bombs — `minor >= 4` (would fail every Jan–Mar under date versions) and `/^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$/` (rejected same-day ordinal releases YYYY.M.D-N). Now asserts date-pattern + exact lockstep with root package.json.\n\n## Deliberate scope boundary\n\nExtension manifests (packages/*/extensions/*/manifest.json + version literals in each extension index.ts) stay at 0.1.0: they are pm-loader-internal metadata pinned by unit specs, not published artifact versions. Follow-up candidate if the policy should extend there.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/sync-versions.mjs check` passes post-apply; `claude plugin validate .` and `... ./plugins/pm-claude --strict` both pass (v2.1.207).\n- vitest: sync-versions (6), run-release-pipeline (33), claude-plugin-contract, pm-mcp-server, session-start, smoke-claude-plugin, release-version, builtin-extension-entrypoints — all green (109+39 tests).\n- eslint clean on all touched files; `node scripts/smoke-claude-plugin.mjs` passes end-to-end."
